parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving

fuel trouble codes (e.g.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake lock-up can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The rear brake pads lock up
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pulsation can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The brake pedal pulsates upon depression
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake master cylinder failure can cause loss of brakes, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes straight to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake booster failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving on steep or slippery roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and powertrain can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

and experiences unusual noises or vibrations.
